cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CR 

The paper focuses on the application of deep learning and computer vision in urban studies, specifically in mapping slums, transport modes, and pedestrians in cities. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category, as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories, which are closely related to deep learning. The paper also involves robotics (cs.RO) in the development of autonomous vehicles for urban transportation. Finally, the paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for object detection and recognition, which falls under the computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CR) category.
